ound:honeyDew;\"|3.1% ''174''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1888 United States presidential election|1888]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|46.3% ''2,742''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''52.5%''' ''3,109''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|1.3% ''75''\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1830= 5476\n|1840= 10042\n|1850= 12428\n|1860= 17865\n|1870= 21133\n|1880= 22777\n|1890= 23867\n|1900= 24594\n|1910= 24813\n|1920= 23887\n|1930= 24864\n|1940= 28276\n|1950= 36108\n|1960= 48198\n|1970= 57022\n|1980= 65088\n|1990= 63657\n|2000= 71435\n|2010= 76794\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=82753\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=PEP_2018_PEPANNRES&prodType=table|title=American FactFinder|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214061229/https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=PEP_2018_PEPANNRES&prodType=table|archive-date=February 14, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=U.S. Decennial Census|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><br />1790-1960<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu|title=Historical Census Browser|publisher=University of Virginia Library|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref> 1900-1990<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/in190090.txt|title=Population of Counties by Decennial Census: 1900 to 1990|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><br />1990-2000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|title=Census 2000 PHC-T-4. Ranking Tables for Counties: 1990 and 2000|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref> 2010-2013<ref name=\"census-quickfacts\"/>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[2010 United States Census]], there were 81,162&nbsp;people, 29,860&nbsp;households, and 20,788&nbsp;families residing in the county.<ref name=\"census-dp1\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US18005\n  |title=DP-1 Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213021643/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US18005\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The population density was {{convert|188.7|PD/sqmi}}. There were 33,098 housing units at an average density of {{convert|81.3|/sqmi}}.<ref name=\"census-density\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18005\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |title=Population, Housing Units, Area, and Density: 2010 - County\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212204146/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18005\n  |archive-date=2020-02-12\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The racial makeup of the county was 89.6% white, 3.4% Asian, 1.8% black or African American, 0.3% American Indian, 0.1% Pacific islander, 3.2% from other races, and 1.6% from two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin made up 6.2% of the population.<ref name=\"census-dp1\"/> In terms of ancestry, 28.5% were [[Germans|German]], 12.4% were [[English people|English]], 12.2% were [[Irish people|Irish]], and 10.7% were [[Americans|American]].<ref name=\"census-dp2\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0400000US18%7c0500000US18005\n  |title=DP02 SELECTED SOCIAL CHARACTERISTICS IN THE UNITED STATES \u2013 2006-2010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214002209/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0400000US18%7C0500000US18005\n  |archive-date=2020-02-14\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\nOf the 29,860&nbsp;households, 34.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 54.1% were married couples living together, 10.7% had a female householder with no husband present, 30.4% were non-families, and 25.3% of all households were made up of individuals. The average household size was 2.53 and the average family size was 3.02. The median age was 38.2 years.<ref name=\"census-dp1\"/>\n\nThe median income for a household in the county was $47,697 and the median income for a family was $64,024. Males had a median income of $50,358 versus $32,334 for females. The per capita income for the county was $26,860. About 7.7% of families and 10.4% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 15.8% of those under age 18 and 5.3% of those age 65 or over.<ref name=\"census-dp3\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0400000US18%7c0500000US18005\n  |title=DP03 SELECTED ECONOMIC CHARACTERISTICS \u2013 2006-2010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214003755/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0400000US18%7C0500000US18005\n  |archive-date=2020-02-14\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nPublic schools in Bartholomew County are administered by the [[Bartholomew Consolidated School Corporation]] and the Flat Rock-Hawcreek School Corporation.  The county's first tuition-free public charter school, the [https://web.archive.org/web/20110721182127/http://www.iscolumbus.org/ International School of Columbus], a middle school/high school, opened in 2009\u201310.  The ISC was an International Baccalaureate World School offering the Diploma Program. The ISC closed due to financial difficulties in the fall of 2013.\n\n[[Ivy Tech Community College Columbus]] is located in Bartholomew County.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ivytech.edu/columbus/index.html|title=Columbus - Ivy Tech Community College of Indiana|website=www.ivytech.edu|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[The Republic (Columbus)|The Republic]]'', daily newspaper covering Bartholomew County\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in Bartholomew County, Indiana]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bartholomew.in.gov Bartholomew County official website]\n*[http://www.bcsc.k12.in.us/ Bartholomew Consolidated School Corporation]\n*[http://www.flatrock.k12.in.us/ Flat Rock-Hawcreek School Corporation]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110721182127/http://www.iscolumbus.org/ International School of Columbus]\n\n{{Geographic location\n|Centre    = Bartholomew County, Indiana\n|North     =\n|Northeast = [[Shelby County, Indiana|Shelby County]]\n|East      = [[Decatur County, Indiana|Decatur County]]\n|Southeast = [[Jennings County, Indiana|Jennings County]]\n|South     = [[Jackson County, Indiana|Jackson County]]\n|Southwest =\n|West      = [[Brown County, Indiana|Brown County]]\n|Northwest = [[Johnson County, Indiana|Johnson County]]\n}}\n\n<!-- Templates -->\n{{Bartholomew County, Indiana}}\n{{Indiana}}\n<!-- Coordinates template -->\n{{coord|39.21|-85.90|display=title|type:adm2nd_region:US-IN_source:UScensus1990}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n<!-- Categories -->\n[[Category:Bartholomew County, Indiana| ]]\n[[Category:Indiana counties]]\n[[Category:1821 establishments in Indiana]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1821]]\n", "name_user": "Whoisjohngalt", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bartholomew_County,_