e]]\"<br/>[[Swing (dance)|Swing]] Marathon / \"[[In the Mood]]\"\n|7<br/>8\n|7<br/>8\n|8<br/>8\n|Safe\n|-\n|7\n|[[Waltz]] / \"[[At This Moment]]\"<br/>Team [[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]] / \"[[Telephone (song)|Telephone]]\"\n|8<br/>9\n|8<br/>9\n|8<br/>9\n|'''Eliminated'''\n|}\n\n=== Season 15 performances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Week#\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Dance / Song\n! colspan=\"3\" |Judges' Score\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Result\n|-\n!Inaba\n!Goodman\n!Tonioli\n|-\n|1\n|[[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]] / \"[[You Know I'm No Good]]\"\n|5.5\n|5.5\n|6\n|'''Eliminated'''\n|}\n\n== ''Danse avec les stars''==\n\n=== Season 9 performances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Week #\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Dance / Song\n! colspan=\"4\" |Judges' Score\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Result\n|-\n![[Patrick Dupond]]\n![[Shy'm]]\n!Chris Marques\n![[Jean-Marc G\u00e9n\u00e9reux]] \n|-\n|1\n|[[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]] / \"[[I'm Every Woman]] / [[Respect]]\" \u2013 [[Aretha Franklin]] \n|7\n|6\n|4\n|5\n|No Elimination\n|-\n|2\n|[[Contemporary]] / \"Pull Marine\" - [[Isabelle Adjani]]\n|9<br>+ 5 bonus \n|8\n|8\n|8\n|Safe \n|-\n|3\n|[[Viennese Waltz]] / \"[[Can't Help Falling in Love]] \" \u2013 [[Elvis Presley]]\n|8\n|8\n|8\n|8\n|Safe\n|-\n|4\n|''Injured''\n|/\n|/\n|/\n|/\n|Safe automatically\n|-\n|5\n|[[Tango]] / \"[[The Addams Family Theme]] - [[Vic Mizzy]]\n|9\n|10\n|9\n|9\n|Safe\n|-\n|6\n|[[Rhumba|Rumba]] / \"[[You Can Leave Your Hat On]]\" - [[Joe Cocker]]\n|10\n|8\n|7\n|8\n|Safe\n|-\n|7\n|[[Contemporary]] / \"[[Earth Song]]\" - [[Michael Jackson]] <br>[[Quickstep]] / \"Moi je joue\" - [[Brigitte Bardot]] \n|9<br>10\n|6<br>8\n|5<br>7\n|6<br>8\n|'''Eliminated'''\n|-\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Accolade\n!Category\n!Result\n!Ref\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Baywatch]]''\n|[[Bravo Otto Award]]\n|[[Bravo Otto|Best Female Television Star]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"10\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000097/awards|title=Pamela Anderson|website=IMDb|access-date=August 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Baywatch]]''\n|[[Bravo Otto Award]]\n|[[Bravo Otto|Best Female Television Star]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1996\n|''[[Barb Wire (film)|Barb Wire]]''\n|[[Bravo Otto Award]]\n|[[Bravo Otto|Best Actress]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1996\n|[[Barb Wire (film)|''Barb Wire'']]\n|[[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards|The Stinkers Bad Movie Award]]\n|[[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards|Worst Actress]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1997\n|{{N/A}}\n|[[Golden Apple Award]]\n|[[Golden Apple Award|Sour Apple]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|1997\n|[[Barb Wire (film)|''Barb Wire'']]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Awards|Golden Raspberry Award]]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst New Star|Worst New Star]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|1997\n|[[Barb Wire (film)|''Barb Wire'']]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Awards|Golden Raspberry Award]]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Actress|Worst Actress]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|1997\n|[[Barb Wire (film)|''Barb Wire'']]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Awards|Golden Raspberry Award]]\n|[[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Screen Combo|Worst Screen Couple]] (shared with her \"Impressive Enhancements\")\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Scooby-Doo (film)|Scooby-Doo]]''\n|[[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards|The Stinkers Bad Movie Award]]\n|[[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards|Most Distracting Celebrity Cameo Appearance]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|2005\n|''[[Stacked]]''\n|[[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award]]\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice TV Actress Comedy|Choice TV Actress - Comedy]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Canadian actors]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book|author=Pamela Anderson|title=Star: a novel|url=https://books.google.com/?id=lpSrZF3h3BQC|year=2004|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-0743493727}}\n* {{cite book|author=Pamela Anderson|title=Star Struck: A Novel|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s7ayNc2vgBoC&pg=PP1|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-0743492836|year=2005}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q83325|b=no|v=no|voy=no|n=no|wikt=no|s=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|0000097|Pamela Anderson}}\n* [http://www.playboy.com/pam-anderson Pamela Anderson] at [[Playboy]] Online\n* {{Curlie|Arts/People/A/Anderson%2C_Pamela/}}\n\n{{Playmates of 1990}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anderson, Pamela}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Actresses of Finnish descent]]\n[[Category:Actresses of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:American cannabis activists]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American television personalities]]\n[[Category:American victims of crime]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Animal rights activists]]\n[[Category:Bigg Boss contestants]]\n[[Category:Canadian cannabis activists]]\n[[Category:Canadian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriate actresses in the United States]]\n[[Category:Canadian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Canadian voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Finnish descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Romani descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Canadian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Finnish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Romani descent]]\n[[Category:Hepatitis survivors]]\n[[Category:HIV/AIDS activists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Cowichan Valley Regional District]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:Footballers' wives and girlfriends]]\n[[Category:People from Ladysmith, British Columbia]]\n[[Category:1990s Playboy Playmates]]\n[[Category:Sexual abuse victim advocates]]\n[[Category:Sports spectators]]\n[[Category:Veganism activists]]\n[[Category:Victims of domestic abuse]]\n[[Category:Women television personalities]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other people}}\n{{Redirect|Pamela Lee|the art historian|Pamela M. Lee}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Short description|Canadian actress and model}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Pamela Anderson\n| image              = Greg and Pamela Anderson (41961859304) (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Anderson in [[New York City]] in June 2018\n| birth_name         = Pamela Denise Anderson\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1967|7|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ladysmith, British Columbia]], Canada\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = Canadian \u2022 American\n| occupation         = {{Flatlist|\n* Actress\n* model\n* novelist\n* activist}}\n| years_active       = 1989\u2013present\n| notable_works      = [[C. J. Parker]] on [[Baywatch]]\n| spouse             = {{Unbulleted list|{{marriage|[[Tommy Lee]]<br>|1995|1998|reason=divorced}}|{{marriage|[[Kid Rock]]<br>|2006|2007|reason=divorced}}|{{marriage|[[Rick Salomon]]<br>|2007|2008|reason={{abbr|ann.|annulled}}}}|{{marriage||2014|2015|reason=divorced}}|{{marriage|[[Jon Peters]]<br>|2020|2020|reason={{abbr|sep.|separated}}}}}}\n| partner            = [[Adil Rami]] (2017\u20132019)\n| children           = 2\n| website            = {{URL|pamelaandersonfoundation.org}}\n| module             = {{Infobox Playboy Playmate | child = yes\n| name        = Pamela Anderson\n| issue       = February 1990\n| bust        = 36 in<ref name=\"playmate\"/>\n| waist       = 24 in\n| hips        = 36 in\n| height      = 5 ft 7 in<ref name=\"playmate\"/>\n| weight      = 103 lb<ref name=\"playmate\"/>\n| preceded    = [[Peggy McIntaggart]]\n| succeeded   = [[Deborah Driggs]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Pamela Denise Anderson''' (born July 1, 1967)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/people/pamela-anderson-9542470|title=Pamela Anderson|website=Biography|accessdate=December 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://www.people.com/people/pamela_anderson/biography/ ''People''].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/pamela-anderson/168778/|title=Pamela Anderson Actor, Model, Producer|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=August 1, 2019}}</ref> is a Canadian actress, model and [[animal rights]] activist. Anderson is best known for her appearances in ''Playboy'' magazine and for her work on the television series ''[[Home Improvement (TV series)|Home Improvement]]'', ''[[Baywatch]]'', and ''[[V.I.P. (TV series)|V.I.P.]]''.\n\nShe initially rose to fame after being selected as the February 1990 [[Playboy Playmate|Playmate of the Month]] for ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine.<ref name=\"playmate\">{{playmate|1990|2}}{{Dead link|date=May 2016}}</ref> Anderson went on to frequent appearances on the magazine's cover, holding the record of the most ''Playboy'' covers by any person.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/pamela-anderson-defends-julian-assange-talks-vladimir-putin-more-1107298|title=Playmate to Politico: How Pamela Anderson Became an International Woman of Mystery|last=Siegel|first=Tatiana|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=May 2, 2018|accessdate=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nShe became known to a wider audience in 1991, appearing as a recurring character, Lisa, on the award-winning [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] comedy series ''[[Home Improvement (TV series)|Home Improvement]]'' for its first two seasons. She received international recognition for her starring role as [[C. J. Parker]] in the action-drama television series ''[[Baywatch]]'', further cementing her status as a [[sex symbol]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/fashion/a23560820/pamela-anderson-chanel-fashion-show/|title=Pamela Anderson Recreates Baywatch at the Chanel Show|last=Ogunnaike|first=Nikki|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/3341731/ns/dateline_nbc/t/pamela-andersons-life-sex-symbol/|title=Pamela Anderson's life as sex symbol|work=[[NBC News]]|date=December 9, 2003|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAnderson has appeared in films such as ''[[Raw Justice]]'' (1994), ''[[Barb Wire (film)|Barb Wire]]'' (1996), and ''[[Blonde and Blonder]]'' (2008). She was inducted into [[Canada's Walk of Fame]] in 2006.<ref name=\"Walk of Fame\">{{cite web|url=http://www.canadaswalkoffame.com/inductees/2006/pamela-anderson|title=Pamela Anderson|publisher=[[Canada's Walk of Fame]]|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAnderson is a prominent activist for the [[animal rights]] movement and has conducted campaigns condemning the commercial fur industry and promoting [[veganism]] through the animal rights organization [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]] (PETA).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://features.peta.org/CrueltyDoesntFly/default.asp|title=Pamela Anderson's 'Cruelty Doesn't Fly' Video|work=[[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]]|accessdate=November 2, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111028000031/http://features.peta.org/CrueltyDoesntFly/default.asp|archivedate=October 28, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAnderson was born in [[Ladysmith, British Columbia]], the daughter of Barry, a furnace repairman, and Carol Anderson, a waitress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/55/Pamela-Anderson.html|title=Pamela Anderson profile at FilmReference.com|publisher=Filmreference.com|accessdate=August 2, 2010}}</ref> Her great-grandfather, Juho Hyyti\u00e4inen, was [[Finnish people|Finnish]] and partly of [[Finnish Kale|Romani]] descent, a native of [[Saarij\u00e4rvi]], and left the [[Grand Duchy of Finland]] (which was a part of the [[Russian Empire]] at the time) for Canada in 1908.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pamwatch.com/nov99.html|title=News|work=PamWatch.com|accessdate=August 2, 2010}}</ref> He changed his name to Anderson when he arrived as an immigrant. Anderson also has [[Russian people|Russian]] ancestry on her mother's side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2008/06/19/pamela_andersons_mom_wish/|title=Pamela Anderson's mom wish|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|date=May 14, 2004|accessdate=June 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAnderson got some press coverage right after her birth as a \"Centennial Baby\", having been born on July 1, 1967, the [[Canadian Centennial|100th anniversary]] of Canada's official founding via the ''[[Constitution Act, 1867]]''.<ref name=\"Walk of Fame\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/centennial-baby-kara-ffolliott-1.4186991|title=Taking the title from Pam Anderson: 1st 'Centennial baby' was born in Regina|last=Johnson|first=Alex|work=[[CBC News]]|date=June 30, 2017|accessdate=March 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAnderson claims she suffered [[Child sexual abuse|sexual abuse as a child]], a fact she revealed publicly in 2014. She said she was molested by a female babysitter from ages 6 to 10, raped by a 25-year-old man when she was age 12, and [[Gang rape|gang-raped]] by her boyfriend and six of his friends when she was 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/celebrity/pamela-anderson-i-was-gang-raped-high-school-abused-kid-n108786|title=Pamela Anderson: I Was Gang Raped in High School, Abused as Kid|work=[[NBC News]]|date=May 19, 2014|accessdate=May 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAnderson attended [[\u00c9cole Highland Secondary School|Highland Secondary School]] in [[Comox, British Columbia]]. During high school, she played on the volleyball team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://offthebench.nbcsports.com/2011/07/01/and-now-pamela-andersons-1983-high-school-volleyball-photo/|title=Off the bench|accessdate=July 28, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606011407/http://offthebench.nbcsports.com/2011/07/01/and-now-pamela-andersons-1983-high-school-volleyball-photo/|archivedate=June 6, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> She graduated in 1985.<ref name=\"Fox News bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/01/03/pamela-anderson-biography/|title=Pamela Anderson's Biography|work=Fox News|date=January 3, 2008|access-date=December 23, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007040009/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/01/03/pamela-anderson-biography/|archivedate=October 7, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 1988, Anderson moved to [[Vancouver]] and worked as a fitness instructor.<ref name=\"Fox News bio\"/>\n\n==Career==\n\n[[File:Pamela Anderson, Beehive.jpg|thumb|upright|Anderson in September 2014]]\n\n===Early modeling===\nIn 1989, Anderson attended a [[BC Lions]] [[Canadian Football League]] game at the [[BC Place|BC Place Stadium]] in Vancouver,<ref name=\"ABCNews14\">{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/models-discovered-chance-encounters/story?id=24511204|title=5 Models Discovered Through Chance Encounters|work=[[ABC News]]|date=July 11, 2014|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref> where she was featured on the [[Jumbotron]] while wearing a [[Labatt]]'s Beer T-shirt.<ref name=\"ABCNews14\"/> The brewing company hired Anderson briefly as a spokesmodel.<ref name=\"ABCNews14\"/> Inspired by that event, her then-boyfriend Dan Ilicic produced a poster of her image, entitled the ''Blue Zone Girl''.<ref name=\"Yahoo Movies\">{{cite web|url=https://movies.yahoo.com/movie/contributor/1800332320/bio|title=Pamela Anderson Biography|publisher=[[Yahoo! Movies]]|accessdate=August 17, 2010}}</ref>\n\nAnderson appeared as the cover girl on ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine's October 1989 issue. She moved to [[Los Angeles]] to further pursue a modeling career. ''Playboy'' subsequently chose her as Playmate of the Month in their February 1990 issue, in which she appeared in the centerfold photo. Anderson then elected to have [[breast implant]] surgery, increasing her bust size to 34D. She increased her bust size again, to 34DD, several years later.<ref name=\"Jeffreys05\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=nTBdDljmslcC&pg=PA160&dq=pamela+anderson+breast+implant#v=onepage&q=pamela%20anderson%20breast%20implant&f=false|title=Beauty and Misogyny: Harmful Cultural Practices in the West|author=Sheila Jeffreys|page=160|publisher=Routledge|location= |isbn=9781134264438|year=2005|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAnderson's ''Playboy'' career spans 22 years, and she has appeared on more ''Playboy'' covers than any other model.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.casinocitytimes.com/news/article/bally-gaming-launches-pamela-anderson-playboy-slot-148379|title=Bally Gaming Launches Pamela Anderson Playboy Slot|work=Casino City Times|date=February 14, 2005|accessdate=February 27, 2009}}</ref> She has also made numerous appearances in the publication's newsstand specials. Anderson wrote the foreword in the ''Playboy'' coffee table book ''Playboy's Greatest Covers''.\n\n===Entertainment career===\nAfter Anderson moved to Los Angeles, she won a minor role as Lisa, the original \"Tool Time girl\", on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] comedy series ''[[Home Improvement (TV series)|Home Improvement]]''. She left the show after two seasons and won the role of [[C. J. Parker]] on ''[[Baywatch]]'', which she played for five seasons between 1992 and 1997 making her one of the longest-serving cast members. This has been one of her best-known roles to date and has gained her a lot of popularity from international viewers. She reprised her role in a reunion movie, ''[[Baywatch: Hawaiian Wedding]]'' (2003), and also to star in commercials for [[DirecTV]] in 2007. Anderson was still modeling for ''Outdoor Life'' and appearing on the cover of the magazine each year. In 1993, Anderson appeared in a music video \"Can't Have Your Cake\" by [[Vince Neil]] to promote his first solo album ''[[Exposed (Vince Neil album)|Exposed]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/people/vince-neil-20638961|title=Vince Neil|work=Biography.com|accessdate=February 19, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220062934/https://www.biography.com/people/vince-neil-20638961|archivedate=February 20, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 1994, she was cast in her first starring film role, in ''[[Raw Justice]]'', also known as ''Good Cop, Bad Cop'', costarring with [[Stacy Keach]], [[David Keith]], and [[Robert Hays]]. Under the alternate title, the film won the Bronze Award at the Worldfest-Charleston in the category for dramatic theatrical films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davidwinterstribute.com/apps/photos/photo?photoid=153194578|title=Worldfest Charleston Good Cop Bad Cop: Reviews and Award|work=DavidWintersTribute.com|date= |accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 1996, she appeared in the film ''[[Barb Wire (film)|Barb Wire]]'' playing Barbara Rose Kopetski, which was later claimed by some sources to be Anderson's real name, although it is not. The movie, a thinly veiled futuristic remake of ''[[Casablanca (film)|Casablanca]]'', was not a commercial success. During filming, she had a real [[barb wire]] tattoo put on her left upper arm as an alternative to having it painted on by make-up artists every day, but had it removed in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timeline.com/barbed-wire-tattoo-abe0edaebcb3|archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20161011225940/https://timeline.com/barbed-wire-tattoo-abe0edaebcb3|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 11, 2016|title=The barbed wire tattoo is back and ready to stab your memory|last=Buck|first=Stephanie|work=Timeline.com|date=October 11, 2016|accessdate=December 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn April 1997, she guest hosted ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''. She appeared on one of two covers for the September issue of ''Playboy''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vintageplayboymags.co.uk/90s/Sept/07.htm|title=Playboy Magazine September 1997 vol.44, no.9|work=Vintage Playboy Magazines|accessdate=February 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220122532/http://www.vintageplayboymags.co.uk/90s/Sept/07.htm|archive-date=February 20, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn September 1998, Anderson starred as Vallery Irons in the [[Sony Pictures Television]] syndicated action/comedy-drama series ''[[V.I.P. (TV series)|V.I.P.]]'' created by [[J. F. Lawton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,972305,00.html|title=New Thrills for Pretty Woman|last=Stein|first=Joel|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=November 8, 1999|volume=154|issue=19|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010220034637/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C33431-1%2C00.html|archivedate=February 20, 2001|url-status=dead}}</ref> Blending action and humor in a fast-paced adventure series, with Anderson often poking fun at her tabloid image, the show explored the exciting and sometimes treacherous lives of the rich and famous.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tv.nytimes.com/show/32003/V-I-P-/overview?scp=3&sq=pamela%20anderson%20VIP%20SHOW&st=Search|title=V.I.P.|last=Martel|first=Ned|work=The New York Times|date=January 12, 2007|accessdate=May 21, 2010}}</ref> The series lasted through a successful four-year run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/article/2000/03/10/new-pamela-anderson-lee/|title=The Squad|last=Svetkey|first=Benjamin|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=March 10, 2000|accessdate=April 4, 2018}}</ref> In 1999, she appeared as a man-eating giantess in the music video for \"[[Miserable (song)|Miserable]]\" by California alternative rock band [[Lit (band)|Lit]]. She appeared on ''[[The Nanny]]'' as Fran Fine's rival, Heather Biblow.<ref name=\"Jeffreys05\"/>\n\n[[File:Pamela anderson house st kilda.jpg|thumb|Sam Newman House features a large image of Anderson's face]]\n[[Sam Newman]] House, a [[Novelty architecture|pop architecture]] building constructed in 2003 in [[St Kilda, Victoria|St Kilda]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia, features a large image of Anderson's face. Sam Newman commissioned local architect [[Cassandra Fahey]] to design the building, and used the image with Anderson's permission. Permits were issued retroactively when it became a major local landmark and won the award for Best New Residential Building in the [[Australian Institute of Architects|RAIA]] [[Victorian Architecture Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monash.edu.au/muma/exhibitions/past/2005/pavilions.html|title=Pavilions for New Architecture, Monash University Museum of Art|publisher=Monash.edu.au|accessdate=August 2, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100731023916/http://www.monash.edu.au/muma/exhibitions/past/2005/pavilions.html|archivedate=July 31, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2004, Anderson returned to the spotlight. In May 2004, she appeared naked on the cover of ''Playboy'' magazine. Later, she posed naked for ''[[Stuff (magazine)|Stuff]]'' and ''[[GQ]]'' magazines.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}} Anderson was also featured on the cover of the fashion magazines ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'', British ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Flare (magazine)|Flare]]'', and ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' Canada and in editorials for Russian ''Elle'' and ''[[V (American magazine)|V]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2015/12/04/Pamela-Andersons-Playboy-covers/1591449257374/|title=Pamela Anderson's Playboy covers|website=UPI|language=en|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, she released the book ''Star'', co-written by Eric Shaw Quinn, about a teenager trying to become famous. After this, she began touring the United States, signing autographs for fans at [[Walmart|Wal-Mart]] stores nationwide. Her second book, the sequel ''Star Struck'', released in 2005, is a thinly veiled look at her life with Tommy Lee and the trials of celebrity life. In April 2005, Anderson starred in a new [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] comedy series ''[[Stacked]]'' as Skyler Dayton, a party girl who goes to work at a bookstore. It was canceled on May 18, 2006, after two seasons, although some episodes were never aired. On August 14, 2005, [[Comedy Central]] created the ''[[Comedy Central Roast#Pamela Anderson|Roast of Pamela Anderson]]'' to honor the [[sex symbol]] for the past decade.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n\n[[File:Pamela Anderson USS Halsey.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Pamela Anderson aboard [[USS Halsey (DDG-97)|USS ''Halsey'']], August 2005]]\nAnderson was named most powerful Canadian in Hollywood in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/pamela-anderson-named-most-powerful-canadian-in-hollywood-1.530291|title=Pamela Anderson named most powerful Canadian in Hollywood|work=[[CBC News]]|date=August 31, 2005|accessdate=October 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2005, [[NBC]] cut off a video of Anderson pole dancing on [[Elton John]]'s \"The Red Piano\". NBC said that the footage was inappropriate for prime time. The video was shown on huge screens during the event, while John played \"The Bitch is Back\". In March 2006, it was announced that Anderson would receive a star on [[Canada's Walk of Fame]] thanks to her many years as a model and actress. She is only the second model to receive a star. In April 2006, Anderson hosted Canada's [[Juno Award]]s, becoming the first non-singer and model to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bce.ca/news-and-media/releases/show/pamela-anderson-to-host-the-2006-juno-awards-on-ctv|title=Pamela Anderson to Host The 2006 JUNO Awards on CTV|work=[[BCE Inc.]]|date=February 27, 2006|accessdate=October 3, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003230902/http://www.bce.ca/news-and-media/releases/show/pamela-anderson-to-host-the-2006-juno-awards-on-ctv|archivedate=October 3, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAnderson appeared in the 2006 mockumentary, ''[[Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan]]'', as the title character becomes obsessed with her, and plans to [[Bride kidnapping|abduct and marry her]]. She appears as herself at a book signing at the end of the film, confronted by Borat in a staged botched abduction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2006/11/10/guide_to_borat/|title=What's real in 'Borat'?|last1=Marchese|first1=David|last2=Paskin|first2=Willa|work=[[Salon (website)|Salon]]|date=November 10, 2006|accessdate=April 27, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228145236/http://www.salon.com/2006/11/10/guide_to_borat/|archivedate=February 28, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nShe performed on February 13\u201314, 2008 in a Valentine's Day striptease act at the [[Crazy Horse (cabaret)|Crazy Horse]] cabaret in [[Paris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-anderson-striptease-idUSL0177816020080201|title=Pamela Anderson to perform at nude revue|work=[[Reuters]]|date=February 1, 2008|accessdate=May 26, 2017}}</ref> Anderson then starred in ''[[E!'s Pam: Girl on the Loose!|Pam: Girl on the Loose]]'', which debuted on August 3, 2008 on [[E!]] in the United States.<ref>{{Citation|title=Pam: Girl on the Loose|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1263776/|access-date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2009, Anderson guest-starred as ''Genie of the Lamp'' in the pantomime ''[[Aladdin]]'' at the [[New Wimbledon Theatre]] in Wimbledon, southwest London, UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/stage/theatre/article6958279.ece|title=Pamela Anderson pops out of the lamp and casts a spell on adoring dads|last=Sherwin|first=Adam|work=The Times|location=London|date=December 16, 2009|accessdate=December 31, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/theatre/review-23784558-pamela-andersons-really-quite-a-game-genie-in-aladdin.do|title=Pamela Anderson's really quite a game genie in Aladdin|last=Hitchings|first=Henry|newspaper=Evening Standard|location=London|date=December 16, 2009|accessdate=December 31, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091220040126/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/theatre/review-23784558-pamela-andersons-really-quite-a-game-genie-in-aladdin.do|archivedate=December 20, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Anderson took over the role from comedian [[Ruby Wax]], with former [[EastEnders]] actress [[Anita Dobson]] and comedian [[Paul O'Grady]] also booked for the role.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aladdin. New Wimbledon Theatre|url=http://www.ambassadortickets.com/928/679/Wimbledon/New-Wimbledon-Theatre/Aladdin|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413145535/http://www.ambassadortickets.com/928/679/Wimbledon/New-Wimbledon-Theatre/Aladdin|archivedate=April 13, 2010|accessdate=December 31, 2009}}</ref> In 2010, she appeared in the short film ''The Commuter'' directed by the [[McHenry Brothers]] and shot entirely on the [[Nokia N8]] smartphone as promotion for the phone in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/the-commuter-reveals-the-potential-of-new-technology-2112931.html|title='The Commuter' Reveals the Potential of New Technology|work=[[The Independent]]|location=UK|first=Jo|last=Caird|date=October 22, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vimeo.com/16307784|title=The Commuter|publisher=[[Nokia]]|accessdate=December 10, 2012}}</ref> Anderson was featured in a beach-themed editorial, shot by [[Mario Testino]] for Brazilian ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]''{{'}}s June 2013 \"Body Issue\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pamela-anderson-bikini-vogue-photos_n_3384626|title=Pamela Anderson Slips On A Red Bikini For Risque Vogue Shoot (NSFW PHOTOS)|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=June 4, 2013|accessdate=June 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Reality television===\n[[File:Pamela Anderson Cannes 2017.jpg|thumb|left|Anderson at the [[2017 Cannes Film Festival]]]]\nIn November 2010, Anderson appeared on ''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 4)|season 4]]'' of ''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Bigg Boss]]'', the Indian version of the ''[[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother]]'' television franchise. She stayed as a guest in the house for three days for a reported sum of [[Indian rupee|Rs.]] 2.5 [[crore]]s (approx [[United States dollar|US$]] 550,000).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-south-asia-11777477|title=Pamela Anderson in Indian TV show|work=[[BBC News]]|date=November 17, 2010}}</ref> Furthering her involvement in the franchise, In September 2011, Anderson took part in the [[Big Brother 2011 (UK)|12th season of ''Big Brother'']] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s149/big-brother/news/a340187/pamela-anderson-does-big-brother-to-meet-new-people-i-have-no-time-for-friends.html|title=Pamela Anderson does Big Brother to meet new people: 'I have no time for friends'|website=Digital Spy|date=September 13, 2011|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref> On September 9, 2012, it was officially announced that she will enter the House in [[Bulgaria]] on September 16, taking part in the fourth season of ''[[VIP Brother 2012 (Bulgaria)|VIP Brother]]'', which is the celebrity spin-off of ''[[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother]]'' in Bulgaria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://novanews.bg/news/view/2012/09/09/35633/\u043f\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043b\u0430-\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0441\u044a\u043d-\u0432\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430-\u0432\u044a\u0432-vip-brother-2012/|title=\u041f\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043b\u0430 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0441\u044a\u043d \u0432\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430 \u0432\u044a\u0432 VIP Brother 2012 - NOVA|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn Day 12 for the ''[[Promi Big Brother (season 1)]]'' in Germany, she entered the house, as a Special Guest Star on the final day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/panorama/Pamela-Anderson-zieht-fuer-David-Hasselhoff-in-den-Big-Brother-Container-id27127027.html|title=Promi Big Brother 2013: Pamela Anderson zieht f\u00fcr David Hasselhoff in den Big-Brother-Container - Promis, Kurioses, TV - Augsburger Allgemeine|publisher=Augsburger-allgemeine.de|language=German|date= |accessdate=February 16, 2015}}</ref> [[David Hasselhoff]], a former ''[[Baywatch]]'' co-star, was a contestant in Day 1 to Day 5.\n\n===''[[Dancing with the Stars]]'' around the world ===\nAnderson was a contestant on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|tenth season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'', partnered with professional dancer [[Damian Whitewood]]. The season premiered on March 22, 2010,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ledger-enquirer.com/2010/03/01/1035334/dancing-with-the-stars-cast-revealed.html|title=Dancing with the Stars 2010 pairings: Celebrities, dancers revealed|last=Minty|first=Dawn|work=Ledger-Enquirer.com|publisher=McClatchy Company|date=March 2, 2010|accessdate=August 2, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100925211633/http://www.ledger-enquirer.com/2010/03/01/1035334/dancing-with-the-stars-cast-revealed.html|archive-date=September 25, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> and after seven weeks, Anderson was eliminated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/moviestvmusic/news/pam-anderson-on-leaving-dwts-i-cant-eat-whatever-i-want-anymore-201055|title=Pam Anderson on Leaving DWTS: \"I Can't Eat Whatever I Want Anymore\"|work=Us Weekly|date=May 5, 2010}}</ref> She also took part in the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 15)|15th season]] all-star edition in 2012 with [[Tristan MacManus]]. Anderson and MacManus were eliminated in the first week of competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/tv/dancing-with-the-stars-all-stars-elimination-first-to-go/|title=Dancing with the Stars All-Stars: Who Went Home First?|last=Shira|first=Dahvi|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 25, 2012|accessdate=December 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2011, she was a contestant on the ''[[Bailando 2011]]'' (Argentina), partnered with professional dancer [[Damian Whitewood]]. She left the competition after 4 weeks.\n\nIn 2018, she was a contestant on the [[Danse avec les stars (France season 9)|ninth season]] of [[Danse avec les stars|French ''Dancing with the Stars'']]. The season premiered on September 29, 2018. After seven weeks, Anderson was eliminated, on November 8, 2018.\n\n===''Dancing on Ice''===\nIn 2013, Anderson appeared on [[Dancing on Ice (series 8)|season 8]] of the British reality TV show ''[[Dancing on Ice]]'', partnered with former winner [[Matt Evers]].<ref name=prov121223>{{cite news|url=https://theprovince.com/entertainment/coming+back+Pamela/7738216/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130204194858/http://www.theprovince.com/entertainment/coming+back+Pamela/7738216/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 4, 2013|title=It's all coming back to Pamela|last=Schaefer|first=Glen|work=[[The Province]]|date=December 23, 2012}}</ref><ref name=ds121217>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.ca/british-tv/s101/dancing-on-ice/news/a445828/dancing-on-ice-2013-lineup-pamela-anderson-anthea-turner-more.html|title='Dancing on Ice' 2013 lineup: Pamela Anderson, Anthea Turner, more|last=Goodacre|first=Kate|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=December 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\n===Animal rights===\nOne of Anderson's campaigns as a member of [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] has been against the use of [[fur]]. In 1999, Anderson received the first [[Linda McCartney]] Memorial Award for animal rights protectors, in recognition of her campaign. In 2003, Anderson stripped down for PETA's \"I'd Rather Go Naked Than Wear Fur\" advertising campaign. On June 28, 2006, Anderson posed naked with other protesters on a window display of the [[Stella McCartney]] boutique in London, England. It was a PETA gala event before the PETA Humanitarian Awards. Anderson went inside the boutique and said she would take her clothes off if the event raised enough money for PETA, which it did. She campaigned against [[KFC|Kentucky Fried Chicken]]. In 2001, Anderson released a letter in support of PETA's campaign against Kentucky Fried Chicken, stating \"What KFC does to 750 million chickens each year is not civilized or acceptable.\" She later made a video about KFC's treatment of chickens.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.KentuckyFriedCruelty.com|title=Kentuckey Fried Cruelty|accessdate=February 26, 2007}}</ref> In January 2006, Anderson requested that the [[Governor of Kentucky]] remove a bust of [[Colonel Sanders]], the founder of KFC, from display but her request was refused even when she offered her own bust in exchange. In February 2006, Anderson decided to [[boycott]] the [[Kentucky Derby]] because of its support for Kentucky Fried Chicken.\n\n[[File:Pamela Anderson FBB Chasse aux phoques 14 f\u00e9vrier 2008 (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Anderson is a prominent activist for the animal rights movement.]]\nShe has also campaigned against [[seal hunting]] in Canada. In March 2006, Anderson asked to speak to [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]] [[Stephen Harper]] about the [[Canada's annual seal hunt|annual seal hunt]] but was refused. In May 2006, she petitioned individuals on the street for their opinion on the Canadian Seal Hunt. In December 2009, Anderson, photographed in a T-shirt with a drawn picture of a seal pup on it, was featured in a new ad campaign for PETA. She appears next to the headline \"Save the Seals\" in the ad and urges the public to help end \"Canada's annual seal slaughter.\" She joined forces with the organization again in a campaign for the boycott of fruit-juice maker [[POM Wonderful|POM]]. The \"Pom Horrible Campaign\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://getactive.peta.org/campaign/pam_vs_pom?qp_source=pamvspomgen?c=pvpwiki|title=PETA|accessdate=July 21, 2009}}</ref> has resulted in the company halting [[Animal testing|animal tests]].\n\nAnderson became the center of controversy when she posed in a bikini nearly nude for a PETA ad that was banned in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], on grounds that the ad was sexist. Anderson retorted saying, \"In a city that is known for its exotic dancing and for being progressive and edgy, how sad that a woman would be banned from using her own body in a political protest over the suffering of cows and chickens. In some parts of the world, women are forced to cover their whole bodies with [[burqa]]s \u2013 is that next? I didn't think that Canada would be so puritanical.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-body/news/pamela-anderson-blocked-from-montreal-event-for-sexist-ad-2010157/|title=Pamela Anderson's Nearly Naked PETA Ad Banned in Canada|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=July 15, 2010|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\nShe became a company spokesperson for FrogAds, Inc. in March 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/entertainment/post/2012/03/pam-anderson-launches-race-car-team-fergie-no-x-factor/1#.T2_6JdUSUoo|title=Pam Anderson launches race car team; Fergie: no 'X Factor'|last=Oldenburg|first=Ann|work=[[USA Today]]|date=March 23, 2012|accessdate=March 26, 2012}}</ref> In February 2014, she stripped for a Valentine's Day-themed ad for PETA, urging dog lovers to cuddle up with their pets during winter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/02/pamela-anderson-strips-naked-for-peta-on-valentines-day/|title=Pamela Anderson Strips naked for PETA on Valentine's Day|work=IANS|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|accessdate=February 15, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906073739/http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/02/pamela-anderson-strips-naked-for-peta-on-valentines-day/|archive-date=September 6, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAnderson has actively campaigned for environmental conservation group [[Sea Shepherd Conservation Society]], has served on the Sea Shepherd Board of Directors and is a spokesperson for the group. She has traveled with the organisation in support of campaigns such as Operation Sleppid Grindini, which monitors the activities of fishermen in the [[Faroe Islands]] as part of the traditional pilot whale drive hunt, an event known as the Grindadrap. She is a close friend of Sea Shepherd founder [[Paul Watson]].\n\nIn July 2015, Anderson wrote an open letter to Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]] asking to prevent the passage of the cargo vessel ''Winter Bay'' with over 1,700 tons of [[fin whale]] meat through the [[Northeast Passage]] to Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://seashepherd.org/news/pamela-anderson-asks-putin-to-stop-whale-meat-smugglers/|title=Pamela Anderson Asks Putin to Stop Whale Meat Smugglers|work=[[Sea Shepherd Conservation Society]]|date=July 7, 2015|accessdate=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pamela Anderson devant les ar\u00e8nes de N\u00eemes le 21 juillet 2017.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.36|Pamela Anderson in front of the [[Arena of N\u00eemes]] in public campaign against [[Bullfighting|bullfights]] (July 21, 2017).]]\nOn April 20, 2009, Anderson first wrote to Vladimir Putin to thank him for banning the slaughter of baby [[harp seal]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peta.org/blog/pamela-putin-teaming-seals/|title=Pamela and Putin: Teaming Up for Seals?|last=Flavell|first=Shawna|work=[[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]]|date=April 20, 2009|accessdate=May 3, 2017}}</ref> On July 8, 2015, Anderson wrote to Putin to save whales.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/272323-pamela-anderson-putin-letter/|title=Pamela Anderson Writes to President Putin on Behalf of Endangered Fin Whales|work=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=May 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3949238/pamela-anderson-vladimir-putin-whales/|title=Pamela Anderson Wants President Vladimir Putin of Russia to Save the Whales|last=Feeney|first=Nolan|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref> On September 3, 2015, Pamela Anderson traveled to Russia to share her thoughts on the problem of endangered species at the Eastern Economic Forum in the Russian city of Vladivostok.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/314306-pamela-anderson-russia-forum/|title=Pamela Anderson Discusses Environment and Climate Change at Russian Forum|work=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=September 3, 2015|accessdate=May 3, 2017}}</ref> On December 15, 2015, Anderson, representing the IFAW organization, met with top Kremlin officials regarding animals rights in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rt.com/news/325023-pamela-anderson-kremlin-meeting/|title=Pamela Anderson Pushing for Animal Rights in Kremlin, Moscow, Russia|work=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=December 7, 2015|accessdate=May 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rbth.com/news/2015/12/07/sergei-ivanov-discuses-amur-tiger-populations-with-pamela-anderson_548369|title=Kremlin's Sergei Ivanov Discusses Amur Tiger Populations with Pamela Anderson|work=[[Russia Beyond The Headlines]]|date=December 7, 2015 |accessdate=May 4, 2017}}</ref> On December 15, 2016, Anderson and IFAW officials, including Elena Zharkova from IFAW Russia, met with Kremlin officials to discuss animal welfare and conservation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifaw.org/canada/news/pamela-anderson-and-ifaw-meet-kremlin-officials-discuss-animal-welfare-and-conservation|title=Pamela Anderson and IFAW Meet With Kremlin Officials to Discuss Animal Welfare and Conservation|work=[[International Fund For Animal Welfare]] (IFAW)|date=December 15, 2016|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/video/world/pamela-anderson-visits-kremlin-to-promote-wildlife-conservation/2016/12/16/48224fb6-c3a2-11e6-92e8-c07f4f671da4_video.html|title=Pamela Anderson Holding Meeting at Kremlin, Moscow, Russia To Promote Wildlife Conservation|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=December 16, 2016|accessdate=May 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.newsweek.com/pamela-anderson-would-gladly-have-russian-passport-532853 |title=Pamela Anderson Would Gladly Have a Russian Passport|magazine=[[Newsweek]]|date=December 16, 2016|accessdate=April 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Julian Assange===\nIn December 2016, in a statement to ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine, Anderson called [[WikiLeaks]] founder [[Julian Assange]] a \"hero\". She stated that he had done everyone \"a great service. Everyone in the world has benefited because of WikiLeaks\". Meanwhile, \"elaborate plots against him and made up sexual allegations could result in him being extradited to the US \u2014 where he would not be treated fairly \u2014 because of his exposure of truths.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Bakkila|first=Blake|url=https://people.com/politics/pamela-anderson-julian-assange-london-embassy-release-statement/|title=Julian Assange and Asks for His Release: 'He Is a Hero'|work=People|date=December 10, 2016|access-date=April 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412132311/https://people.com/politics/pamela-anderson-julian-assange-london-embassy-release-statement/|archive-date=April 12, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> In April 2019, over several tweets, Anderson was angry at Assange's ejection from London's [[Embassy of Ecuador, London|Ecuadorian embassy]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Mitchell|first=Robert|url=https://variety.com/2019/politics/news/pamela-anderson-attacks-u-k-following-julian-assange-arrest-1203186699/|title=Pamela Anderson Attacks U.K. Following Julian Assange Arrest|work=Variety|date=April 11, 2019|access-date=April 12, 2019}}</ref> In May 2019, Anderson visited Assange in [[HM Prison Belmarsh|HMP Belmarsh]] with [[Kristinn Hrafnsson]] and said she believed Assange to be innocent and \"a good man... an incredible person. I love him, I can't imagine what he has been going through.\"<ref name=\"itv.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.itv.com/news/2019-05-07/he-is-a-good-man-i-love-him-actress-pamela-anderson-declares-her-support-for-julian-assange-after-prison-visit/|title='He is a good man, I love him': Actress Pamela Anderson declares support for Julian Assange after Belmarsh prison visit|website=ITV News|language=en|access-date=May 7, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"itv.com\"/>\n\nIn October 2019, Anderson announced she will be travelling to Australia in November 2019 to challenge [[Prime Minister of Australia|Australian Prime Minister]] [[Scott Morrison]] to stand up for [[Julian Assange]]. In her announcement she referenced the 'disparaging remarks' he made about her in 2018 and challenged him to debate the matter 'in front of the Australian people'. She also wrote another letter to Scott Morrison asking him to use his influence to secure Assange's release. Morrison replied by letter saying that his government would respect Britain's judicial process and Assange would not receive any special help. In the text of a speech she had intended to give at [[Parliament House, Canberra]], Anderson claimed that Mr Assange was suffering \"psychological torture\" in jail and that \"every moment he is in there, he is in danger\". <ref>{{cite news |last1=Jackson |first1=Steve |title=Scott Morrison responds to Pamela Anderson\u2019s Julian Assange plea |url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/nation/scott-morrison-responds-to-pamela-andersons-julian-assange-plea/news-story/ff122bb5d32842ee9fd630e188945e9d |accessdate=November 26, 2019 |publisher=The Australian |date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> During her visit to Australia she also filmed a television commercial for Australian brand [[Ultra Tune]]. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Anderson |first1=Pamela |title=ULTRA TUNE SIGNS PAMELA ANDERSON FOR LATEST IN THE SERIES OF UNEXPECTED SITUATIONS TELEVISION COMMERCIALS (TVC\u2019s) AND PAMELA CHALLENGES SCOTT MORRISON TO STAND UP FOR JULIAN ASSANGE |url=https://www.pamelaandersonfoundation.org/news/2019/10/9/ju5adnmxb7far8nvmd2cv2df8wrctn |website=www.pamelaandersonfoundation.org}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|last=Workman |first=Alex |title=Pamela Anderson\u2019s baying letter to Scott Morrison for Julian Assange |url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/commentary/strewth/pamela-andersons-baying-letter-to-scott-morrison-for-julian-assange/news-story/b143b84b7b2cdacd90dfafe51eebf308 |accessdate=November 17, 2019 |work=The Australian |date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===AIDS and other activism===\nIn March 2005, Anderson became a spokesperson for [[Make-up Art Cosmetics|MAC Cosmetics]]'s MAC AIDS Fund, which helped people affected by AIDS and HIV. After becoming the official spokesmodel, Anderson raised money during events in Toronto, Tokyo, Dublin, and Athens. Anderson became the celebrity spokesperson for the [[American Liver Foundation]], and served as the Grand Marshal of the SOS motorcycle ride fundraiser.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hepatitiscfree.com/messages/2002/dec232002.htm|title=Pamela Anderson and Kid Rock raise money for Hepatitis C research|website=hepatitiscfree.com|access-date=March 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Anderson wrote an open letter to President [[Barack Obama]] urging the legalization of [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]].<ref>Anderson, Pamela (February 2009). ''[[Playboy]]'', p. 112.</ref>\n\nAnderson has also shown support to the [[Friends of the Israel Defense Forces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jewishjournal.com/news/los_angeles/140356/moving-and-shaking-fidf-gala-texas-holdem-poker-classic-our-house-and-more/|title=Moving and shaking: FIDF Gala, Texas Hold'em Poker Classic, Our House and more|last=Torok|first=Ryan|work=[[The Jewish Journal of Greater Los Angeles]]|date=November 13, 2014|accessdate=May 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, Anderson, a close friend of [[Sea Shepherd Conservation Society]] founder [[Paul Watson]], and a longtime supporter and advisory board member of that organization, became a full board member, in order to further its efforts in opposing the hunting of whales.<ref>[http://www.seashepherd.org/news-and-commentary/news/pamela-anderson-joins-board-of-directors-of-sea-shepherd-conservation-society.html \"Pamela Anderson Joins Board of Directors of Sea Shepherd Conservation Society\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170423061929/http://www.seashepherd.org/news-and-commentary/news/pamela-anderson-joins-board-of-directors-of-sea-shepherd-conservation-society.html |date=April 23, 2017 }}. [[Sea Shepherd Conservation Society]]. December 1, 2015.</ref>\n[[File:DiEM25 Pamela Anderson Berlin 2019.jpg|thumb|Pamela Anderson featuring on a DiEM25 poster in Berlin during the German 2019 EU electoral campaign.]]\nIn November 2016, Anderson starred in a video public service announcement<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KwGs9Du9NUc|title=The Driving Game|date=November 2, 2016|accessdate=November 3, 2016}}</ref> produced by the [[National Limousine Association]] and the [[National Sexual Violence Resource Center]] as part of the Ride Responsibly initiative, titled The Driving Game, which aimed to shed light on the lack of universal driver regulations in the private ground transportation industry.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.multivu.com/players/English/7769451-nla-ride-responsibly-driving-game-psa|title=Pamela Anderson Calls for Increased Safety Regulations for Ride-Hailing Apps in Anti-Sexual Assault PSA|publisher=[[PR Newswire]]|date=November 2, 2016|accessdate=November 3, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103135412/http://www.multivu.com/players/English/7769451-nla-ride-responsibly-driving-game-psa/|archivedate=November 3, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAnderson once again starred in a video public service announcement<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/bb9ZxP4rgSk|title=The Signs|date=January 8, 2018|accessdate=January 11, 2018}}</ref> produced by the [[National Limousine Association]] in January 2018, this time in partnership with Promoting Awareness | Victim Empowerment (PAVE), as part of the Ride Responsibly initiative. Titled The Signs, the PSA aims to continue to push for passenger safety and universal driver regulations in the private ground transportation industry.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.multivu.com/players/English/8098851-nla-ride-responsibly-pave-psa-the-signs/|title=Pamela Anderson Takes On Ride-Hail Apps in #MeToo Campaign|publisher=[[PR Newswire]]|date=January 8, 2018|accessdate=January 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter supporting the [[yellow vests movement]] in [[France]], Anderson attended a meeting of the [[European Spring (political party)|European Spring]] with [[Yanis Varoufakis]] and [[Benoit Hamon]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://diem25.org/diem-25-atterrit-a-bruxelles-pour-lancer-la-premiere-liste-transnationale-europeenne//|title=DiEM 25 atterrit \u00e0 Bruxelles pour lancer la premi\u00e8re liste transnationale europ\u00e9enne! |date=March 2019|accessdate=March 25, 2019}}</ref> She appeared as a supporter on election posters of the German DiEM25 campaign in the run-up to the 2019 European Elections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://diem25.org/pamela-anderson-supports-democracy-in-europe-diem25/|title=Pamela Anderson supports democracy in Europe \u2013 DiEM25|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n===Relationships===\nAnderson married [[Tommy Lee]], drummer of [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]], on February 19, 1995, after knowing him for about 96 hours, or 4 days.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/pamela_anderson/biography/ |title=Pamela Anderson Biography |last=Anderson|first=Pamela |magazine=People.com |accessdate=February 16, 2015}}</ref> They wed on a beach, with Anderson in a bikini. Anderson's mother did not know, and learned of the marriage from ''People'' magazine. During this time, she was known professionally as Pamela Anderson Lee. They have two sons together: Brandon Thomas (born June 5, 1996)<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/bay-watch-ends-happily-article-1.717816|title=Bay(by) Watch Ends Happily| first=A.J.|last=Benza|work=[[New York Daily News|Daily News]]|location=New York City|date= June 6, 1996|accessdate= March 8, 2018|archivedate=March 8, 2018|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20180308185638/http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/bay-watch-ends-happily-article-1.717816 |url-status=live}}</ref><!--information released to media by the parent's representative--> and Dylan Jagger (born December 29, 1997).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/12/31/nyregion/chronicle-860271.html|title=Chronicle|first=Nadine|last=Brozan|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=December 31, 1997|accessdate=March 8, 2018|archivedate=March 8, 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180308191735/http://www.nytimes.com/1997/12/31/nyregion/chronicle-860271.html|url-status=live}}</ref> During their tumultuous marriage, Lee was arrested for [[Domestic violence|spousal abuse]] after assaulting Anderson. He was sentenced to six months in the Los Angeles County Jail.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://people.com/music/tommy-lee-pamela-anderson-painful-past-and-new-drama/|title=Inside Pamela Anderson and Tommy Lee's Painful Past and New Family Drama: 'He Feels Like She Crossed a Line'|last=K.C. Baker|first=Janine Rubenstein|date=March 9, 2018|website=People|access-date=}}</ref><!--information released to media by the parent's representative--> The couple divorced in 1998.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6479855/tommy-lee-pam-anderson-marriage-anniversary|title=Tommy Lee & Pam Anderson Married 20 Years Ago Today|last=Lynch|first=Joe|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 19, 2015|accessdate=March 8, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616035204/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6479855/tommy-lee-pam-anderson-marriage-anniversary|archivedate=June 16, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2002, Anderson publicly stated that she had contracted [[hepatitis C]] by sharing tattoo needles with Lee, and began writing a regular column for ''[[Jane (magazine)|Jane]]'' magazine. In October 2003, Anderson jokingly said on [[Howard Stern]]'s radio show that she does not expect to live more than 10 or 15 years,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pamelaanderson.com/news/news.asp?item=2056|title=Pamela Anderson Official Site and Fan Club |publisher=News Headlines Television Tabloids Magazines|accessdate=February 1, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041029141238/http://www.pamelaanderson.com/news/news.asp?item=2056|archivedate=October 29, 2004}}</ref> but this was misconstrued and taken seriously by many websites and tabloids. As of 2015, Anderson was cured of hepatitis C.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/article/pamela-anderson-cured-hepatitis-c-increase-environmental-activism|title=Pamela Anderson Says She Got Her Life Back After Being Cured of Hep C: 'They Told Me I Would Die in 10 Years'|last=Park|first=Andrea|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=November 24, 2015|accessdate=December 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pamela Anderson and Kid Rock.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Anderson and [[Kid Rock]] in 2003]]\nAfter the 1998 divorce, Anderson became engaged to the model [[Marcus Schenkenberg]]; they broke up in 2001. She then became engaged to the singer [[Kid Rock]] (Robert J. Ritchie); she broke up with him in 2003. On July 18, 2006, it was announced that she would marry Kid Rock on July 29, 2006, on a yacht near [[Saint-Tropez]], France. \"Feels like I've been stuck in a time warp,\" said Anderson in her blog entry. \"Not able to let go of MY family picture&nbsp;... it's been sad and lonely and frustrating&nbsp;... I've raised my kids alone in hope of a miracle. Well my miracle came and went. And came back and back because he knew that I'd wake up one day and realize that I was waiting for nothing.\" \"I'm moving on,\" she declared. \"I feel like I'm finally free&nbsp;... I'm in love.\" There was extensive unconfirmed media speculation that the marriage was pregnancy-related, but the theory was based only on Anderson's representative's refusal to comment on the question.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pattayadailynews.com/shownews.php?IDNEWS=0000000731|title=Pamela Anderson Mum on Rumors of Pregnancy Motivating Kid Rock Marriage|work=Pattaya Daily News|archivedate=March 14, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070314080129/http://www.pattayadailynews.com/shownews.php?IDNEWS=0000000731}}</ref>\n\nOn November 10, 2006, it was announced that Anderson had miscarried while in Vancouver shooting a new film, ''[[Blonde and Blonder]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pamela Anderson Suffers a Miscarriage|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1557773,00.html|work=People.com|publisher=Time Inc|accessdate=August 2, 2010|date=November 10, 2006}}</ref> Seventeen days later, on November 27, 2006, Anderson filed for divorce in Los Angeles County Superior Court, citing irreconcilable differences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/news/ah2832.shtml|title=Access Hollywood|accessdate=February 26, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070712233524/http://www.accesshollywood.com/news/ah2832.shtml|archivedate=July 12, 2007}}</ref> Some news reports have suggested that Kid Rock's outrage during a screening of ''[[Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan|Borat]]'', in which Anderson has a cameo role, led to the filing for divorce two weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/features/news/2006/11/061128_pamkidrock/ |title=Spin.com |accessdate=February 26, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070319104503/http://www1.spin.com/features/news/2006/11/061128_pamkidrock/ |archivedate=March 19, 2007 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2007, Anderson said that she often had sex with Lee since their divorce.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://divertissement.sympatico.msn.ca/Nouvelles/NouvellesCelebrites/ContentPosting.htm?newsitemid=2635&feedname=TQS_FR&show=true&number=3&showbyline=false&abc=abc |publisher= MSN.ca |title= Pamela Anderson de retour avec Tommy Lee? |date=February 14, 2007 |accessdate= February 24, 2017 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070419055944/http://divertissement.sympatico.msn.ca/Nouvelles/NouvellesCelebrites/ContentPosting.htm?newsitemid=2635&feedname=TQS_FR&show=true&number=3&showbyline=false&abc=abc |archivedate= April 19, 2007 }}</ref> In June 2008, Lee said that they were trying again to make things work together.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/celebrity/pamela-anderson-tommy-lee-back-together-again/|title=Pamela Anderson and Tommy Lee Back Together Again, but mostly for the children|last=Wells|first=Melody S.|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=June 13, 2008|accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2007, Anderson stated on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' that she was engaged. On September 29, Anderson and film producer [[Rick Salomon]] applied for a marriage license in Las Vegas.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/7021566.stm Anderson to marry Paris Hilton ex] BBC News&nbsp;\u2013 October 1, 2007</ref> On October 6, 2007, Anderson married Salomon in a small wedding ceremony at [[The Mirage]], between her two nightly appearances at the [[Planet Hollywood Resort and Casino]] in [[Hans Klok]]'s magic show.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gray |first=Mark |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20151049,00.html |title=Pamela Anderson Weds Rick Salomon&nbsp;\u2013 Weddings, Pamela Anderson, Rick Salomon |work=People|date=October 7, 2007 |accessdate=August 2, 2010}}</ref> The couple separated on December 13, and on February 22, 2008, Anderson requested through the courts that the marriage be [[Annulment|annulled]], citing fraud.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2008-02-26-pamela-anderson_N.htm|title=Anderson seeks annulment of marriage to Salomon|work=USA Today|date=February 26, 2008|accessdate=August 2, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2013, Anderson stated on ''The Ellen DeGeneres Show'' that she and Salomon were \"friends with benefits\". In January 2014, she announced that she had remarried Salomon on an unspecified date.<ref name=eonline-jan2014>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/498233/pamela-anderson-remarries-ex-husband-rick-salomon|title=Pamela Anderson Remarries Ex-Husband Rick Salomon|author=Fowler, Brandi|publisher=E! Online|date=January 11, 2014|accessdate=January 11, 2014}}</ref> Anderson filed for divorce from Salomon in February 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bacardi|first1=Francesca|title=Pamela Anderson Files for Divorce From Rick Salomon for the Third Time|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/625131/pamela-anderson-files-for-divorce-from-rick-salomon-for-the-third-time|accessdate=February 12, 2015|publisher=[[E!]] ([[NBCUniversal]]) |date=February 12, 2015|location=United States}}</ref> The divorce was finalized on April 29, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/pamela-anderson-rick-salomon-finalize-divorce|title=Pamela Anderson and Rick Salomon Finalize Second Divorce, Apologize for 'Hurtful Comments'|last=Kimble|first=Lindsay|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=April 29, 2015|accessdate=May 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAnderson began dating French footballer [[Adil Rami]] in 2017. In late June 2019, Anderson declared on an Instagram post that the relationship with Rami was over.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/pamela-anderson-adil-rami-cheating-domestic-abuse|title=Pamela Anderson dumps soccer star boyfriend Adil Rami, accuses him of cheating, abuse|last=Sager|first=Jessica|work=[[Fox News]]|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019}}</ref> On January 20, 2020 Anderson married her boyfriend, Hollywood producer [[Jon Peters]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-xl/lifestyle/celebs/pamela-anderson-marries-jon-peters/ar-BBZc51C?li=BBKhQr3|title=Pamela Anderson marries Jon Peters|website=www.msn.com|access-date=January 24, 2020}}</ref> On February 1, 2020, Anderson announced she and Peters had separated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1118540/pamela-anderson-and-jon-peters-split-12-days-after-secretly-getting-married|title=Pamela Anderson and Jon Peters Split 12 Days After Getting Married|last=Morin|first=Alyssa|date=February 1, 2020|publisher=[[E! News]]|language=en-US|access-date=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Legal issues===\nA [[Celebrity sex tape|sex tape]] of Anderson and Tommy Lee on their honeymoon was stolen from their home in 1995 and made a huge stir on the Internet. Anderson sued the video distribution company, [[Seth Warshavsky|Internet Entertainment Group]]. Ultimately, the Lees entered into a confidential settlement agreement with IEG. Thereafter, the company began making the tape available to subscribers to its web sites again, resulting in triple the normal traffic on the sites.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pelline|first=Jeff|title=Pamela Lee drops video case|url=http://news.cnet.com/Pamela-Lee-drops-video-case/2100-1023_3-205848.html?tag=mncol|work=CNET News|publisher=CBS Interactive|date=December 1, 1997|accessdate=August 2, 2010}}</ref> Another tape, which was made before the Tommy Lee tape, involving Anderson and musician [[Bret Michaels]] from [[Poison (American band)|Poison]], was later announced, and an abridged version of less than 60 seconds appeared on the internet. Frames of the video first appeared in ''[[Penthouse (magazine)|Penthouse]]'' magazine in March 1998. The tape was successfully blocked by Michaels, but a four-minute sex tape is still available on the Internet.{{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n===Citizenship and homes===\nAnderson became a [[Naturalization|naturalized citizen]] of the United States in 2004, while retaining her Canadian citizenship.<ref>[http://www.today.com/popculture/pamela-anderson-becomes-u-s-citizen-wbna4962472 \"\"]. ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today]]''. [[NBC]]. May 12, 2004.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywood.com/celebrities/pamela-anderson-57303964/|title=Pamela Anderson|work=[[Hollywood.com]]|accessdate=February 24, 2017}}</ref> Anderson purchased a beach home in [[Malibu, California]], for $1.8 million in 2008 and attempted to sell it in 2013 for $7.75 million, but later took it off the market.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/realestate/hot-property/la-fi-hotprop-pamela-anderson-malibu-lease-20180912-story.html|title=Pamela Anderson looks to rent Malibu beach house for $40,000 a month|work=LA Times|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref> Since then, she is renting out her Malibu home for $50,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/pamela-andersons-malibu-home|title=Pamela Anderson\u2019s Malibu Home is renting for $50,000 per month|work=Architectural Digest|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref> per month and moved to the [[French Riviera]], mainly because of her relation with the [[Association football|football]] player [[Adil Rami]]. Anderson previously lived in a mansion in [[Cassis]], in the commune of [[Marseille]], [[France]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.fr/20180130/pamela-anderson-moves-in-frances-so-called-murder-capital|title=Former Baywatch star Pamela Anderson sets up home in Marseille|work=TheLocal.fr|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QmhEEd9a450|title=From Playboy to Politics - inside the extraordinary life of Pamela Anderson|work=60 Minutes Australia|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref> As of July 25, 2019, Anderson said she was again living in her home country after \"recently moving back to my beautiful native Canada.\" and later revealed that she's residing on [[Vancouver Island]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pamelaandersonfoundation.org/news/2019/7/25/gvv0n0mgfli6h3rycnc10find6tri9|title=Letter to The Honorable Jason Kenney Premier of Alberta and The Honorable Devin Dreeshen Minister of Agriculture and Forestry Province of Alberta|website=Pamela Anderson|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://torontosun.com/entertainment/celebrity/pamela-anderson-on-baywatch-justin-trudeau-playboy-and-being-exactly-where-she-wants-to-be|title=Pamela Anderson on Baywatch, Justin Trudeau, Playboy and being exactly where she wants to be|last=Daniell|first=Mark|work=[[Toronto Sun]]|date=August 21, 2019|accessdate=September 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914132326/https://torontosun.com/entertainment/celebrity/pamela-anderson-on-baywatch-justin-trudeau-playboy-and-being-exactly-where-she-wants-to-be|archive-date=September 14, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Veganism===\nAnderson is a [[Veganism|vegan]], an advocate for [[animal rights]], and an active member of the animal protection organization [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]] (PETA), taking part in several campaigns for animal rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegnews.com/articles/page.do?pageId=2549&catId=8|title=Pamela Anderson's Vegan Diet|last=Pope|first=Gabrielle|work=[[VegNews]]|date=September 27, 2010|accessdate=September 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.feministezine.com/feminist/ecofeminism/Id-Rather-Go-Naked-Than-Wear-Fur.html|title=I'd Rather Go Naked Than Wear Fur|work=Feministezine.com|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref> She became a vegetarian in her early teens when she saw her father cleaning an animal he had hunted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.healthylivingmagazine.us/Articles/559/|title=Pamela Anderson \u2013 Bomb Out Of The Shell|last=Mandeville|first=Yana|publisher=Healthy Living Magazine|accessdate=January 20, 2015}}</ref> In the [[2019 Canadian federal election]] she endorsed the [[Green Party of Canada]].<ref name=\"Globalnews01\">{{cite news |last1=Boynton |first1=Sean |title=Pamela Anderson tours Vancouver Island hometown to campaign with Greens |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6023856/pamela-anderson-ladysmith-green-party/ |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |publisher=Global News |date=October 11, 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|1